definition.value: A trisaccharide consisting of three beta-D-xylose units connected via (1->4)-linkages.
A trisaccharide consisting of three alpha-D-glucose units connected via (1->3) linkages. Also known as alpha-nigerotriose.
A trisaccharide consisting of three alpha-L-arabinose units connected via (1->5) linkages.
An organic radical derived from ethane.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of cis-heme d hydroxychlorin gamma-spirolactone.
Any additive that enhances the efficiency of fuel.
An alkane that consists of pentane bearing two methyl substituents at position 2 and a single methyl substituent at position 4.
A metallochlorin that is the iron(II) complex of 7,8-dihydroporphyrin which is substituted by methyl groups at positions 3, 7, 7, 8, 12, 13, and 17, and by carboxyethyl groups at positions 2 and 18.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the removal of a proton from both of the carboxy groups of iron methylchlorin. Major species at pH 7.3.

A metallochlorin that is ferroheme b which is hydroxylated at positions 5 and 6, and in which the resulting 6-hydroxy group undergoes formal condensation with the carboxy group of the 6-carboxyethyl group to afford the corresponding spirolactone in which the oxygen atoms at positions 5 and 6 are trans to each other.
A monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of a proton from the carboxylic acid group of trans-heme d hydroxychlorin gamma-spirolactone.

label.value: cis-heme d hydroxychlorin gamma-spirolactone methyl ester

definition.value: A carboxylic ester that is the methyl ester of cis-heme d hydroxychlorin gamma-spirolactone.
A metallochlorin that is ferroheme b which is cis-dihydroxylated at positions 5 and 6.
A metallochlorin that is ferroheme b which is trans-dihydroxylated at positions 5 and 6.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the removal of a proton from both of the carboxy groups of heme d trans-diol.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the removal of a proton from both of the carboxy groups of heme d cis-diol.
A two-membered oligosaccharide sulfate that consists of 2-O-sulfo-L-idopyranuronic acid having a 2-deoxy-6-O-sulfo-2-(sulfoamino)-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl residue attached at the 4-position.
The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of palmitic acid.

A three-membered linear oligosaccharide sulfate that consists of a 2-O-sulfo-L-idopyranuronic acid residue flanked by two 6-O-sulfo-2-(sulfoamino)-D-glucopyranose residues, connected via alpha-(1->4)-linkages.
A two-membered oligosaccharide sulfate that consists of 2-deoxy-6-O-sulfo-2-(sulfoamino)-D-glucose having an alpha-L-idopyranuronosyl residue attached at the 4-position.

A glycosaminoglycan composed of a backbone of repeating beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine units joined by (1->4)-linkages. The capsular polysaccharide produced by the E. coli K5 strain.

A sulfated glycosaminoglycan composed of a backbone of repeating beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine units, variably O-sulfated at the 6-position of the glucosamine residues and joined by (1->4)-linkages. The structure provided is representative and shows the most common repeating unit

A sulfated glycosaminoglycan composed of a backbone of repeating beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1->4)-N-sulfonyl-alpha-D-glucosamine units, variably O-sulfated at the 6-position of the glucosamine residues and joined by (1->4)-linkages. The structure provided is representative and shows the most common repeating unit
A C-nitro compound that consists of nitrobenzene bearing a bromomethyl substituent at the para-position.
An organobromine compound that consists of pentanedinitrile bearing bromo and bromomethyl substituents at position 2.
A triol obtained by sequential periodate-oxidation and borohydride-reduction of guanosine.
A pyrazolopyrazole that consists of 1H,7H-pyrazolo[1,2-a]pyrazole-1,7-dione bearing three methyl substituents at positions 2, 5 and 6 as well as a bromomethyl substituent at the 3-position.
Any organic heterobicyclic compound class containing two ortho-fused pyrazole rings.
A pyrazolopyrazole that consists of 1H,7H-pyrazolo[1,2-a]pyrazole-1,7-dione bearing two methyl substituents at positions 2 and 6 as well as two bromomethyl substituents at positions 3 and 5.
A pyrazolopyrazole that consists of 1H,7H-pyrazolo[1,2-a]pyrazole-1,7-dione bearing four methyl substituents at positions 2, 3, 5 and 6.
The nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the dianion formed from dTDP-4-dehydro-beta-L-rhamnose by loss of two protons from its diphospho group.  Intermediate in dTDP-rhamnose biosynthesis.

A sialohexaosylceramide consisting of a linear heptasaccharide made up from one glycolylneuraminyl residue, three galactose residues, two N-acetylglucosamine residues and one glucose residue, which at the reducing end is attached to the ceramide portion via a beta-linkage.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate having myristoyl (tetradecanoyl) as the 1-O-acyl group.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate having linoleyl (9Z,12Z-octadecadienoyl) as the 1-O-acyl group.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate having 18-mercaptooctadecanoyl as the 1-O-acyl group.

A nucleoside residue in which an adenosine residue has been modified by substitution at C-2 by a methylthio (methylsulfanyl) group and at the 6-amino nitrogen by a cis-4-hydroxy-Delta(2)-isopentenyl group.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate having oleoyl as the 1-O-acyl group.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 2,3-cyclic phosphate having oleoyl as the 1-O-acyl group.
A monoacylglycerol phosphate that consists of sn-glycerol 2,3-cyclic phosphate bearing an acyl group at position 1.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate having lauroyl (dodecanoyl) as the 1-O-acyl group.

A heterodetic cyclic peptide comprising a cyclopentapeptide made up from L-seryl, L-tyrosyl, L-phenylalanyl, L-isoleucyl and L-methoionyl residues and cyclised by formation of an ester bond between the carboxy group of the methionyl residue and the side-chain hydroxy group of the seryl residue. In addition, the exocyclic amino group is acylated by an L-cysteinylamino)ethoxy]ethoxy}acetyl)-L-tyrosyl-L-seryl-L-threonyl group.

A beryllium molecular entity consisting of beryllium (+2 oxidation state) and oxide in the ratio 1:1. In the solid state, BeO adopts the hexagonal wurtzite structure form while in the vapour phase, it is present as discrete diatomic covalent molecules.
A compound of beryllium (+2 oxidation state) and chloride in the ratio 1:2.
A 3-hydroxy steroid resulting from deoxygenation at position 17 of estradiol or estrone.
A 4-hydroxy steroid that consists of 17beta-estradiol having an additional hydroxy group at position 4.
Any steroid bearing a 4-hydroxy substituent.
A 4-hydroxy steroid that consists of 17beta-estradiol bearing an additional 6alpha-hydroxy substituent.
A 4-hydroxy steroid that consists of 17beta-estradiol bearing an additional 11beta-hydroxy substituent.
A 3-hydroxy steroid that is obtained by formal dehydration at the 17-position of estradiol.
